module.exports={"coco-palm-vs-sugar-beach-viceroy-resort": {"keyDifferences": "Coco Palm is a mid-range family all-inclusive in Rodney Bay, Saint Lucia's busiest tourist corridor, with a gym, diving, spa, horseback riding, and evening entertainment. Its beach rating of 4 and pool rating of 5.8 are notably weak, though its value (8.8), cleanliness (8.7), and service (8.6) scores are strong for the price. Sugar Beach, A Viceroy Resort is a premium family resort set between the Pitons in Soufriere, with a heated pool, kids club, yoga, snorkelling, tennis, fishing, hiking, and babysitting. Its ratings are uniformly exceptional: location 9.8, atmosphere 9.5, cleanliness 9.7, room 9.6, and beach 8.5 \u2014 every category where Coco Palm underperforms, Sugar Beach excels. The overall gap of 8.7 versus 9.4 reflects a fundamentally different tier of experience. Coco Palm suits guests who want a convenient Rodney Bay base at fair value; Sugar Beach suits those willing to pay a premium for one of the Caribbean's most dramatic natural settings and a polished, full-service resort to match.", "whoShouldChooseA": "Budget-conscious families or couples who want a clean, well-serviced Saint Lucia base in lively Rodney Bay, with easy access to restaurants, nightlife, and the island's north, and who prioritise value over a standout beach or pool experience.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Families and couples who want an elite Saint Lucia resort set dramatically between the Pitons, with a world-class beach, heated pool, kids club, babysitting, and an atmosphere and location that rank among the Caribbean's very best, and who are willing to pay for it.", "whenToVisit": "Both resorts benefit from Saint Lucia's dry season, mid-December through mid-April, when rainfall is lowest and humidity most manageable. Rodney Bay's Coco Palm is well-positioned for the Jazz and Arts Festival in May. Sugar Beach in Soufriere sits in a rain shadow and can be visited more comfortably year-round, though the Piton views are sharpest in the dry season.", "activities": "At Coco Palm guests can dive, ride horses, and explore Rodney Bay's marina, bars, and shopping. At Sugar Beach guests dive, snorkel, hike the Pitons UNESCO trail, fish, play tennis, and take yoga classes within the resort, with the drive-in volcano and Sulphur Springs at Diamond Falls a short trip from Soufriere. Both offer spa services and evening entertainment on-site."}, "bay-gardens-beach-resort-vs-sugar-beach-viceroy-resort": {"keyDifferences": "Both resorts are family-friendly Saint Lucia all-inclusives with kids clubs, diving, snorkelling, spas, and babysitting, but they sit in very different tiers on nearly every measurable dimension. Sugar Beach, A Viceroy Resort scores 9.4 overall against Bay Gardens Beach Resort's 8.6, and the gaps widen sharply across atmosphere (9.5 vs 6.9), pool (8.7 vs 6.0), beach (8.5 vs 7.5), food (8.9 vs 7.2), and room quality (9.6 vs 8.5). Sugar Beach sits in Soufriere, tucked between the Piton mountains on a private white-sand cove that earns a near-perfect 9.8 for location \u2014 one of the most dramatic resort settings in the Caribbean. Bay Gardens is in Rodney Bay, a convenient, commercial strip that scores 8.7 for location but lacks the wow factor. Bay Gardens counters with watersports equipment rentals and rooms for large groups in a more accessible, sociable northern setting. Sugar Beach adds tennis, hiking, and fishing alongside its luxury infrastructure. If you want convenience and value in Rodney Bay, choose Bay Gardens. If you want one of Saint Lucia's most spectacular resort experiences between the Pitons, choose Sugar Beach.", "whoShouldChooseA": "Families and groups who want a solid, well-priced Saint Lucia all-inclusive in the busy, convenient Rodney Bay area, with watersports rentals, evening entertainment, and large-group rooms without paying top-tier luxury prices.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Families and couples who want an exceptional, design-forward Saint Lucia luxury resort set dramatically between the Pitons on a private cove, with outstanding food, a heated pool, hiking, tennis, fishing, and one of the most visually stunning locations in the Caribbean.", "whenToVisit": "Both resorts benefit from Saint Lucia's dry season between December and April, when rainfall is lowest and sunshine most reliable. Sugar Beach's Soufriere location on the leeward west coast stays relatively sheltered even during wetter months. Rodney Bay at Bay Gardens can be livelier and more social over holiday periods. Avoid peak hurricane season, August through October, at either property.", "activities": "At Bay Gardens in Rodney Bay, guests are steps from the island's busiest marina, restaurant strip, and shopping, with watersports rentals, diving, and snorkelling on-site. Sugar Beach in Soufriere offers on-site hiking trails toward the Pitons, tennis, fishing, diving, and snorkelling in some of Saint Lucia's richest marine waters, with the Sulphur Springs and Diamond Falls botanical gardens a short drive away."}, "sugar-beach-viceroy-resort-vs-zoetry-marigot-bay-st-lucia": {"keyDifferences": "Sugar Beach, A Viceroy Resort and Zo\u00ebtry Marigot Bay St. Lucia are both luxury Saint Lucia all-inclusives at the same price level, but they diverge sharply in setting, ratings, and amenity depth. Sugar Beach sits in the Soufri\u00e8re valley between the Pitons, earning a near-perfect location score of 9.8 versus Zo\u00ebtry's 8.8, and a dramatically higher beach rating of 8.5 against Zo\u00ebtry's 2.5 \u2014 indicating Zo\u00ebtry is a marina-fronting property without a meaningful beach. Sugar Beach's overall rating of 9.4 outpaces Zo\u00ebtry's 8.6, with a particularly strong atmosphere score of 9.5 versus 8.6 and rooms at 9.6 versus 8.8. Sugar Beach also offers a far broader activity roster \u2014 kids club, diving, snorkelling, yoga, hiking, tennis, and evening entertainment \u2014 while Zo\u00ebtry's amenities are limited to a gym, spa, swim-up bar, fishing, buffet, and babysitting. Both share identical value scores of 8.3, but Sugar Beach delivers considerably more for that rating. Zo\u00ebtry edges Sugar Beach slightly on sleep quality (9.2 vs 9.1) and cleanliness (9.2 vs 9.7).", "whoShouldChooseA": "Families and couples who want one of Saint Lucia's most iconic settings \u2014 a rainforest valley framed by the Pitons \u2014 combined with a full suite of activities including diving, hiking, yoga, tennis, and a kids club, and who prioritise beach access and atmosphere over quiet seclusion.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Families or couples drawn to the intimate, yacht-dotted atmosphere of Marigot Bay who prioritise tranquillity and sleep quality over beach access or activity variety, and who are comfortable with a marina-front setting rather than a traditional shoreline.", "whenToVisit": "Both resorts benefit from Saint Lucia's dry season, running mid-December through mid-April, when rainfall is minimal and humidity is manageable. Sugar Beach's Soufri\u00e8re location sits on the drier leeward coast, making it slightly more sheltered year-round. Zo\u00ebtry at Marigot Bay is similarly leeward-facing. Shoulder months of May and November offer lower rates with acceptable weather at both properties.", "activities": "Sugar Beach guests can dive and snorkel directly off the property, hike through rainforest to the Pitons, take yoga classes, play tennis, and join evening entertainment programs. Day trips to Soufri\u00e8re town, the sulphur springs, and the botanical gardens are minutes away. Zo\u00ebtry guests are best placed for fishing excursions and exploring Marigot Bay's sailing scene, with spa treatments and the swim-up bar as the primary on-site draws."}, "secrets-st-lucia-resort-and-spa-vs-sugar-beach-viceroy-resort": {"keyDifferences": "Both resorts sit in Saint Lucia at the same $$$$ price point, but they diverge sharply on experience and target guest. Secrets St. Lucia is an adults-only all-inclusive on the island's northern end, scoring a solid 8.6 overall with strong service (9.2) and cleanliness (9.1), but its beach (6.8) and pool (7.6) ratings lag noticeably. Sugar Beach, A Viceroy Resort is a family-friendly property tucked between the Pitons in Soufriere, posting a 9.4 overall with a near-perfect location score (9.8), exceptional atmosphere (9.5), room quality (9.6), and a beach rating of 8.5 \u2014 a full 1.7 points above Secrets. Sugar Beach's amenity list is substantially deeper: diving, snorkelling, hiking, tennis, fishing, yoga, a kids club, and babysitting versus Secrets' headline differentiator of reservation-free dining. Secrets wins on value perception (8.6 vs. 8.3) and delivers a quieter, couples-focused all-inclusive stay, while Sugar Beach commands a premium for its dramatic Pitons setting, broader activity roster, and higher scores across nearly every category.", "whoShouldChooseA": "Adults-only couples or groups who want a classic all-inclusive format in Saint Lucia \u2014 unlimited food and drink without booking restaurants in advance \u2014 and prioritise excellent service and sleep quality over a picture-perfect beach or a long activity menu.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Families and couples who want one of the Caribbean's most dramatic natural settings, nestled between the Pitons on a dark-sand beach, with a full suite of activities including diving, hiking, tennis, and a kids club, and are willing to pay for a property that scores at the top of nearly every category.", "whenToVisit": "Saint Lucia's dry season runs mid-December through April, making it the prime window for both resorts. Sugar Beach sits on the wetter, more lush western leeward coast near Soufriere, so rainfall is more frequent year-round but typically brief. Secrets, further north, sees slightly drier conditions. Both resorts are busiest and most expensive over the Christmas\u2013New Year period.", "activities": "Sugar Beach guests can dive, snorkel, hike the Piton trails, fish, play tennis, and practise yoga, all framed by UNESCO World Heritage scenery. The Soufriere area also offers the drive-in Sulphur Springs volcano and botanical gardens nearby. Secrets guests have a quieter activity footprint, with access to the water at their location, though the northern resort corridor provides easy access to Rodney Bay's marina, bars, and shopping."}, "bay-gardens-marina-haven-hotel-vs-sugar-beach-viceroy-resort": {"keyDifferences": "Both resorts sit in Saint Lucia, but they occupy entirely different tiers. Sugar Beach, A Viceroy Resort scores 9.4 overall versus Bay Gardens Marina Haven Hotel's 8.1, and the gaps widen dramatically on the experiential metrics that matter most: beach (8.5 vs. 2.5), pool (8.7 vs. 5.1), atmosphere (9.5 vs. 6.1), and food (8.9 vs. 6.2). Sugar Beach is set between the Pitons in Soufriere, a location rated 9.8, with villa-style rooms rated 9.6, a full spa, kids club, diving, snorkelling, hiking, babysitting, and tennis in one of the Caribbean's most photogenic settings. Bay Gardens Marina Haven is a marina-side family property with stronger value (8.1) and cleanliness (8.5) scores but limited beach access and a more functional than aspirational atmosphere. Sugar Beach commands a $$$$ price point against Bay Gardens' $$$, and the ratings justify the premium across almost every category. If you want a world-class Saint Lucia resort with extraordinary location, rooms, and food, Sugar Beach wins decisively. If budget is the primary constraint and a marina setting is acceptable, Bay Gardens offers clean, serviceable accommodation.", "whoShouldChooseA": "Budget-conscious families or couples visiting Saint Lucia who prioritise clean, well-serviced accommodation at a marina location over beach access or resort atmosphere. Those using the property as a base for island exploration rather than an immersive resort experience will find Bay Gardens' value score of 8.1 hard to argue with.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Families and couples seeking a top-tier Saint Lucia resort experience between the Pitons, with exceptional rooms, food, beach, and atmosphere to match a $$$$ price point. Those who want kids club, babysitting, diving, snorkelling, hiking, spa, and tennis in a genuinely stunning natural setting.", "whenToVisit": "Saint Lucia's dry season runs January through April, offering the most reliable sunshine for both properties. Sugar Beach's Soufriere location on the leeward west coast stays relatively sheltered year-round, making it more forgiving during the wetter months of July through November. Bay Gardens sits further north near Rodney Bay, where conditions are similarly seasonal. Both benefit from the December to April peak window.", "activities": "Sugar Beach guests can dive and snorkel directly off the property's beach, hike to the Pitons, take yoga classes, fish, play tennis, and explore Soufriere's volcanic landscape including the drive-in volcano and Diamond Falls nearby. Bay Gardens marina guests are well-placed for Rodney Bay's sailing scene, water taxis to Pigeon Island National Landmark, and easy access to the north's restaurants and nightlife."}, "hideaway-at-royalton-saint-lucia-vs-sugar-beach-viceroy-resort": {"keyDifferences": "Both resorts sit in Saint Lucia at the same price tier, but they diverge sharply on nearly every measurable dimension. Sugar Beach, A Viceroy Resort outscores Hideaway at Royalton across the board: overall rating 9.4 vs 8.1, beach 8.5 vs 6.0, atmosphere 9.5 vs 7.4, location 9.8 vs 8.2, and room quality 9.6 vs 8.6. Sugar Beach sits in the Piton Valley near Soufri\u00e8re, one of the Caribbean's most dramatic settings, with volcanic sand beach, jungle villas, and direct views of the UNESCO-listed Pitons. Hideaway at Royalton is an adults-only property in Cap Estate in the island's north, stronger on sleep quality (8.6) and cleanliness (8.8), but its beach score of 6.0 signals a meaningful limitation. Hideaway suits couples wanting a quieter northern escape; Sugar Beach suits families and couples willing to pay for an exceptional sense of place, with a fuller amenity set including kids club, babysitting, hiking, diving, tennis, and fishing that Hideaway does not match.", "whoShouldChooseA": "Adults-only couples or solo travelers who want a polished northern Saint Lucia retreat with strong room quality, cleanliness, and service scores, and are less focused on a world-class beach or landmark scenery. Good for those who prioritize a quieter, well-maintained property over dramatic natural setting.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Families and couples who want one of the Caribbean's most visually spectacular resort settings, with Piton views, a volcanic beach, jungle villas, and a full amenity suite including kids club, babysitting, diving, hiking, and tennis. Guests who value atmosphere and location above all else will find Sugar Beach hard to rival.", "whenToVisit": "Saint Lucia's dry season runs January through April, offering the most reliable sunshine at both resorts. Sugar Beach's Soufri\u00e8re location on the leeward west coast stays calmer in light winds year-round, making it workable outside peak season. Cap Estate in the north can catch more trade wind chop. Both resorts see higher rates and demand over Christmas and New Year.", "activities": "Sugar Beach guests can dive, snorkel, hike toward the Pitons, fish, play tennis, join yoga classes, and explore Soufri\u00e8re's sulphur springs and botanical gardens nearby. Hideaway at Royalton's activity listing is less detailed, but Cap Estate's northern position gives guests access to championship golf at Royalton's adjacent course, and Rodney Bay's marina, restaurants, and nightlife are a short drive away."}, "royalton-saint-lucia-vs-sugar-beach-viceroy-resort": {"keyDifferences": "Royalton Saint Lucia is a family all-inclusive in the northern Cap Estate area with beach access and solid room and service scores, but relatively modest ratings across food (7.5), beach (6.0), pool (7.1), and atmosphere (7.1). Sugar Beach, A Viceroy Resort sits in the dramatic Soufri\u00e8re valley between the Pitons on the island's southwest coast, and it outscores Royalton in nearly every measurable category: overall 9.4 vs 8.0, food 8.9 vs 7.5, beach 8.5 vs 6.0, atmosphere 9.5 vs 7.1, location 9.8 vs 8.2, and room 9.6 vs 8.6. Sugar Beach also carries a vastly deeper amenity set including a kids club, spa, diving, snorkelling, yoga, hiking, tennis, fishing, babysitting, heated pool, and evening entertainment. Royalton offers a more conventional north-coast all-inclusive experience at the same price tier, while Sugar Beach delivers one of the Caribbean's most scenically distinctive resort settings with premium service to match. The gap between these two same-priced resorts is substantial across almost every dimension.", "whoShouldChooseA": "Families who want a straightforward north Saint Lucia all-inclusive with easy access to Rodney Bay's restaurants, nightlife, and shopping, and who prioritise strong room quality and service scores over destination drama or a wide amenity range.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Families and couples who want a once-in-a-lifetime Caribbean setting between the Pitons, with a full luxury amenity suite including diving, snorkelling, spa, kids club, and yoga, and are willing to accept Soufri\u00e8re's remoteness in exchange for scenery and atmosphere rated near-perfect by guests.", "whenToVisit": "Both resorts benefit from Saint Lucia's dry season running mid-December through April, when rainfall is lowest and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Sugar Beach's Soufri\u00e8re location sits on the wetter, more lush southwest coast, so the dry season advantage is especially pronounced there. Royalton's Cap Estate location in the north is marginally drier year-round. Both resorts see peak pricing over Christmas and New Year.", "activities": "Royalton guests are well-placed for Rodney Bay marina, Pigeon Island National Landmark, and the island's main nightlife strip. Sugar Beach guests can snorkel and dive directly off the resort's volcanic-sand beach, hike to sulphur springs, take guided Piton treks, and explore Soufri\u00e8re town. Sugar Beach's on-site offering of tennis, fishing, yoga, and evening entertainment means fewer reasons to leave the property."}, "sugar-beach-viceroy-resort-vs-the-soco-house": {"keyDifferences": "Both are premium Saint Lucia all-inclusives at the same price level, but their ratings diverge sharply in almost every category. Sugar Beach sits in the shadow of the Pitons in Soufri\u00e8re with an overall rating of 9.4 versus The Soco House's 7.9. The gap is most dramatic in atmosphere (9.5 vs 7.1), location (9.8 vs 8.1), beach (8.5 vs 3.5), and pool (8.7 vs 5.6). Sugar Beach's room score of 9.6 and cleanliness of 9.7 also outpace Soco House's 8.0 and 8.6 respectively. Sugar Beach carries a full amenity roster including a kids club, spa, diving, hiking, yoga, tennis, fishing, and babysitting in one of the Caribbean's most dramatic natural settings. The Soco House's beach score of 3.5 and pool score of 5.6 suggest guests expecting strong water-based facilities will be disappointed. Soco House's value rating of 7.9 matches Sugar Beach's 8.3 reasonably closely, but given the wide performance gaps, Sugar Beach delivers considerably more for the premium price point.", "whoShouldChooseA": "Families and couples who want one of the Caribbean's most spectacular resort settings, with the Pitons as a backdrop, a full activity program including diving, hiking, and spa, and consistently outstanding room quality and service. Guests willing to pay a premium for a genuinely memorable luxury experience.", "whoShouldChooseB": "Guests who prioritise cleanliness, solid sleep quality, and a quieter, more low-key Saint Lucia stay without heavy reliance on beach or pool facilities. Best suited to those spending most of their time exploring the island rather than anchored to resort amenities.", "whenToVisit": "Saint Lucia's dry season runs from December through May, when rainfall is minimal and trade winds keep temperatures comfortable. Both resorts benefit from this window. The wet season from June through November brings lower rates and fewer crowds, though brief tropical showers are common. Hurricane season peaks August through October, carrying some weather risk for either property.", "activities": "Both resorts are positioned to access Saint Lucia's rich landscape. Sugar Beach offers on-site diving, snorkelling, hiking, tennis, and fishing, with the Piton peaks and Sulphur Springs volcano minutes away. Guests at either property can arrange day trips to Marigot Bay, the rainforest interior, Jade Mountain, and local fishing villages, with sailing and whale-watching charters operating island-wide."}}
